{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/backup-your-business","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"1d1ef86c-5c9f-54d3-b4a7-4c1927bad4c2","name":"backup-your-business","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/backup-your-business.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/7pOBftbT1BMM3WnRw35V0x/545804defef1478725e19b4762b041ef/backup-your-business.jpg?w=500&h=305","alt":"Five Days' Backup"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software is an amazing thing: a few thousand lines of text can power an entire\nbusiness. One thing should be obvious: make sure you never lose the source code\nof your business. This is something your technical co-founder will take care of\nfrom day one. And that creates a problem that I want to shed some light on."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Making proper backups of software is a complicated task. And it usually involves\nsetting up tools and processes that are created with developers in mind. It\ninvolves things like encryption, off-site copies, grandfathers, fathers and\nsons."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"If one day you and your technical co-founder part ways in a bad way, you will\nfind it impossible to get hold of a copy of your companies most valuable asset\nthat can be used to keep operating your business with another partner."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"You can prepare for this unlikely event, though. Do it in the beginning of your\nbusiness and your technical co-founder will happily assist you in setting this\nup. He gets another level of safety and if you are not in an evil mindset there\nis no real argument why not to constantly ensure every co-founder of a business\nhas unlimited access to a copy of the current source code."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Your mileage may vary but here are some practical ideas how to set up an easy to\nuse system:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"If you can, open-source your software and put it on GitHub. Make sure that\nthis is your primary source code repository used by the development team to\nensure it's up to date all the time."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Have a daily ZIP archive of all your source code on a backup server. Make sure\nthat this server is rented by your company not by your co-founder or his\nbuddies. If you don't mind third-parties snooping through your files, use\nGoogle Drive, Dropbox or Amazon S3 for the backup. Then make daily backups of\nthe files there to storage devices that only you have access to (flashdisk,\nexternal hard drives or your laptop)."}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Trust but verify"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":": Let a tech-savvy friend you trust verify the backups you\nhave once in a while to get the extra certainty that you can't be left out in\nthe cold."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[],"tagName":"hr","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Photo credits:\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Five Days' Backup"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/daryl_mitchell/1199598508","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" by\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"daryl_mitchell"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.flickr.com/photos/daryl_mitchell/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" (CC BY-SA 2.0)"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"Backup your business: Advice for non-technical co-founders","subtitle":null,"noheadline":null,"date":"2015-03-07T22:30:00.000Z","abstract":"How to make sure you never lose the source code of your business.\n","lang":null},"headings":[]}},"Footer":{"id":"cfe5b9e2-511c-5615-992a-dab82e1f8ed7","name":"Footer","relativeDirectory":"","relativePath":"Footer.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT sol